ava database driver; its advertised usage is creating a Driver against bolt://localhost:7687 and executing Cypher, so meaningful coverage of the main Driver/session/query path needs a Neo4j server beyond the normal scaffold.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"docker_image\",\n      \"image\": \"neo4j:5.26-community\",\n      \"slug\": \"neo4j-5-26-community\",\n      \"reason\": \"A real Neo4j DBMS is needed to exercise the primary GraphDatabase.driver, connection, session, and executableQuery APIs; 5.26 is a Neo4j 5 LTS/community image compatible with the 5.x Java driver line.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For any real-query test, start the allowed Neo4j container with authentication such as NEO4J_AUTH=neo4j/testpassword, publish Bolt port 7687 to a free localhost port, wait until Bolt accepts connections, then connect with GraphDatabase.driver(\\\"bolt://localhost:<port>\\\", AuthTokens.basic(\\\"neo4j\\\", \\\"testpassword\\\")). Always close Driver/Session objects and remove the container in teardown. No extra Maven dependency is required if tests use docker via ProcessBuilder.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The current failing repository tests exercise value/object mapping and do not require a Neo4j server; Docker-backed coverage should not be added if the fix can stay focused on that Java runtime failure.\",\n    \"Neo4j container startup can be slower than pure unit tests, so tests need a bounded readiness wait and reliable cleanup.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_02be191aabd3ea7e016a428e4314388190b758379314aca083\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1831, "output": 881, "cacheRead": 39424, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 42136, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782746677895, "responseId": "resp_02be191aabd3ea7e016a428e365f408190be2128f89712741b"}}
